Key Match Events: The match ended in no result due to rain
Pre-Game Insights: South Africa have never lost a T20I to Zimbabwe, with their last meeting in 2018 ending in a Zimbabwean defeat.
Zimbabwe's Sikandar Raza has been in excellent form, scoring 652 T20I runs at an average of 40.75 this year.
South Africa's captain Temba Bavuma is under pressure due to his poor form and recent injuries.
Zimbabwe's coach Dave Houghton has brought back the element of fun and given players freedom to perform.
The match is significant for both teams as it marks the start of the Super 12s for South Africa and Zimbabwe's first major tournament under Houghton.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The teams have not met at a T20 World Cup since 2012.
Luke Jongwe is two away from 50 T20I wickets.
